transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Yeah, thanks for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I have a question about the product.

Speaker 1: Yeah, what's going on?

Speaker 2: I ordered some and it came today.

Speaker 1: But when I read it, it appears to me that it's generic Viagra.

Speaker 2: I thought I was getting the new Viagra.

Speaker 1: What's your last name, sir?

Speaker 2: Rotman, R-O-T-T-M-A-N.

Speaker 1: What's your first name?

Speaker 2: John.

Speaker 1: Alrighty, John. Let's see what's going on.

Speaker 2: And do you have those pills there in front of you, Mr. Rotman?

Speaker 1: No, I don't. They're upstairs.

Speaker 2: Okay, if you could grab them for me, I can double check and make sure you got the correct thing.

Speaker 1: If you didn't, I'll send you out a replacement order, of course. No problem.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: I'll have to go upstairs.

Speaker 2: Yeah, please let me know what the markings on the pills say when you get them.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Give me about one minute, okay? Take your time.

Speaker 1: Okay, what are you looking for?

Speaker 2: Let me know what the markings on the actual physical pills say, Mr. Rotman.

Speaker 1: Well, it's kind of a four-sided pill.

Speaker 2: Take your time.

Speaker 1: It is so hard for me to see, sir.

Speaker 2: Let me get a magnifying glass.

Speaker 1: Take your time.

Speaker 2: No.

Speaker 1: No, I got it.

Speaker 2: AC339.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so those definitely are incorrect, Mr. Rotman.

Speaker 2: Those are very similar to the pills that we give guys at the VA and things like that, but that's not the AGB.

Speaker 1: Most likely a machine error.

Speaker 2: What I will have to do for you, of course, I'll have to replace this order.

Speaker 1: I'm going to send you out a new one.

Speaker 2: It'll be there in the next few days.

Speaker 1: I'm really sorry about that, Mr. Rotman.

Speaker 2: You'll see when this order comes out.

Speaker 1: The markings on the pills will be different, and the label will have a different indication as well.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: What do I do with these?

Speaker 2: You can throw them away if you want.

Speaker 1: You can flush them.

Speaker 2: You can save them for a rainy day.

Speaker 1: They're yours.

Speaker 2: You don't have to send them back or anything.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Well, I appreciate it.

Speaker 1: Have a good day.

Speaker 2: Yeah, no problem.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye now.
